## Classifier Prompt Reliability Notes

Testing with Llama 3.2 3B, here are expected classifications:

| Message | hasDocument | Expected Intent |
|---------|-------------|-----------------|
| "Encode this" | true | ENCODE_DATA |
| "Process the grades in this file" | true | ENCODE_DATA |
| "" (empty, document attached) | true | ENCODE_DATA (via fast-path) |
| "What's trending on Twitter?" | false | SUMMARIZE_TWITTER |
| "Show me the latest tweets" | false | SUMMARIZE_TWITTER |
| "What's happening on X?" | false | SUMMARIZE_TWITTER |
| "Explain photosynthesis" | false | ANSWER_ASSIGNMENT |
| "How do I solve quadratic equations?" | false | ANSWER_ASSIGNMENT |
| "Help me with my lesson plan on fractions" | false | ANSWER_ASSIGNMENT |
| "Good morning!" | false | CHAT |
| "How are you?" | false | CHAT |
| "What can you do?" | false | CHAT |

The JSON schema constraint (`enum` on the `intent` field) means the model literally cannot output any value other than the four valid intents. This is the single most important reliability mechanism and is far superior to regex parsing of free-text output.
